cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "The Street Code"
message: "If you cite or reference this work, please use the metadata below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: McColery
    given-names: Jimmy
url: "https://github.com/jimmymccolery/the-street-code"
repository-code: "https://github.com/jimmymccolery/the-street-code"
abstract: >-
  The Street Code is a methodology research repository documenting a personal
  AI-discipline framework: cross-substrate audit chains, canonical-state
  discipline, framework-encoded verification, and the empirical fires through
  which the framework's rules earned their current shape. The corpus is
  operator-audit-shaped (memory-keeping and audit trail for the operator's own
  methodology research arc); public availability enables discoverability for
  others researching similar territory.
keywords:
  - ai-methodology
  - llm
  - cross-substrate-verification
  - canonical-state
  - audit-chain
  - anti-patterns
  - solo-indie-development
  - procedural-characters
  - active-inference
  - cross-cultural-disclosure
  - research-notes
license: MIT
date-released: "2026-05-02"
